  Merlin! (time=10)\nPlease wait at the bar\,\nparty Sir Lancelot of 2 peop
 le. (time=12)\nTable for Arthur Pendragon! (time=15)\nPlease wait at the b
 ar\,\nparty The Green Knight of 3 people. (time=17)\nTable for Sir Lancelo
 t! (time=20)\n** Simulation Terminated **\n\nThe average waiting time was:
  7.28\nThe following parties were never seated:\nparty The Green Knight of
  3 people\n\nHave a nice meal!\n\nExtra Credit (5 points)\n\nModify the A 
 command to include a tip/bribe for the Maitre De. The new format would the
 n be:\n\nA t n b name\n\nwhere b is the amount of the bribe\, in Euros\, o
 f course. A party is then placed in line ahead of everyone who gave a less
 er bribe. Two parties that bribe the same amount are placed in order of ar
 rival. Modify the input file to include bribes for a sample run\, and prin
 t the total bribe money collected as part of the final summary.\n\nNote: T
 his is not trivial. Do not start this until the rest is working correctly.
  You will have to change some aspects of the Queue implementation to get t
 his to work.\n\n \n\nTo get started:\n\n1.  Make a new folder for this a
 ssignment.    \n\n2.  Write a class called Party.  What information d
 o we need to store about each party?  Write getters and setters for these
  variables.  Then write main and test your getters and setters.\n\n3.  N
 ext work on reading input from the file. \n\n* Start by reading the items
  in the first line of the file in and printing them all out.   To get ju
 st a single String (instead of a whole line at once)\, use:  inputFileSca
 nner.next()\;\n\n* Now try to read the items in the first three lines of t
 he file in and then printing them all out.  \n\n* Now add a loop so that
  you read lines until you encounter the Q (for quit).\n\n4.  Copy these f
 iles into your folder and compile them.  Then create a new QueueLL object
 . \n\n* [AbstractDataType.java] (https://butler.instructure.com/courses/5
 4110/pages/abstractdatatype-dot-java)\n\n* [Queue.java] (https://butler.in
 structure.com/courses/54110/pages/queue-dot-java)\n\n* [QueueLL.java] (htt
 ps://butler.instructure.com/courses/54110/pages/queuell-dot-java)\n\n5.  
  Next\, modify the code you wrote in Step 3\, so that if you read a line 
 that starts with A you create a new Party object using your setters and en
 queue it.  Then try dequeue-ing it and printing it using your getters.  
  Note: When you call dequeue\, it returns a generic Object.  You will n
 eed to cast this so that it is of type Party.  \n\n6.  Once that's work
 ing\, see if you can enqueue all the parties in the file.  \n\n7.  To c
 ompute the average waiting time\, keep track of the total number of people
  seated\, and keep track of the total time spent waiting using something l
 ike this:\n\ntotmins = totmins + partysize*(tos - toa)\n\nwhere tos is the
  time of seating\, and toa is the time of arrival. Since you need to know 
 both times\, this must be done when the party is seated.
